## 4. SERVER-SIDE REQUEST FORGERY (SSRF)

**Title:** Unrestricted Server-Side Requests via Link Scraper  
**CVSS Score:** 8.6 (High)  
**CWE:** CWE-918  
**OWASP:** A10:2021 – Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF)  

### Description

The `/links` endpoint accepts a URL parameter and fetches content from that URL without validation. This allows attackers to:
- Access internal services and metadata services
- Scan internal network and enumerate services
- Read internal files via `file://` protocol
- Perform port scanning
- Access cloud metadata (AWS, Azure, GCP)

**Vulnerable Code Location:** `src/main/java/com/scalesec/vulnado/LinkLister.java` (Line 9-19)

```java
@RestController
@EnableAutoConfiguration
public class LinksController {
  @RequestMapping(value = "/links", produces = "application/json")
  List<String> links(@RequestParam String url) throws IOException{
    return LinkLister.getLinks(url);  // No validation!
  }
}

public static List<String> getLinks(String url) throws IOException {
  List<String> result = new ArrayList<String>();
  Document doc = Jsoup.connect(url).get();  // Fetches any URL
  Elements links = doc.select("a");
  for (Element link : links) {
    result.add(link.absUrl("href"));
  }
  return result;
}
```

### Impact

- **AWS Metadata Access:** Extract IAM credentials, instance roles, secrets
- **Internal Database Access:** Connect to MongoDB, PostgreSQL, Redis on private IPs
- **Internal Service Enumeration:** Discover internal applications and services
- **Port Scanning:** Map internal network topology
- **Local File Access:** Read sensitive files via `file://` protocol
- **DOS Attack:** Force server to consume bandwidth/resources
- **Credential Disclosure:** Access internal configuration services

### Mitigation

1. **URL Whitelist:** Maintain list of allowed domains (recommended)
2. **URL Validation:** Reject private IP ranges before request
3. **Disable Dangerous Protocols:** Block `file://`, `gopher://`, `data://`
4. **Network Segmentation:** Firewall internal services from application
5. **Request Timeouts:** Set strict timeout on outbound requests
6. **Rate Limiting:** Limit number of requests per user/IP

**Remediation Code:**

```java
public static List<String> getLinks(String url) throws BadRequest {
  try {
    URL aUrl = new URL(url);
    String host = aUrl.getHost();
    
    // Check for private IPs and localhost
    if (host.equals("localhost") || 
        host.startsWith("127.") || 
        host.startsWith("172.") || 
        host.startsWith("192.168") || 
        host.startsWith("10.")) {
      throw new BadRequest("Private IP not allowed");
    }
    
    // Check for potential metadata services
    if (host.contains("169.254.") || host.contains("metadata")) {
      throw new BadRequest("Metadata services not allowed");
    }
    
    // Only allow HTTP/HTTPS
    String protocol = aUrl.getProtocol();
    if (!protocol.equals("http") && !protocol.equals("https")) {
      throw new BadRequest("Only HTTP/HTTPS allowed");
    }
    
    // Even better: use whitelist
    Set<String> allowedDomains = new HashSet<>(
      Arrays.asList("wikipedia.org", "github.com", "stackoverflow.com"));
    
    if (!allowedDomains.contains(host)) {
      throw new BadRequest("Domain not whitelisted");
    }
    
    return LinkLister.getLinks(url);
  } catch (Exception e) {
    throw new BadRequest(e.getMessage());
  }
}
```

