1. **Use Whitelist Approach:** Only allow specific domains (recommended)
2. **Use InetAddress Canonicalization:** Resolve hostname to verify IP
3. **Check All IP Ranges:** Loopback, link-local, multicast, reserved
4. **Validate After Redirect:** Check final URL after redirects
5. **DNS Rebinding Protection:** Time-based verification

**Remediation Code:**

```java
public static List<String> getLinksV2(String url) throws BadRequest {
  try {
    // Whitelist of allowed domains
    Set<String> ALLOWED_DOMAINS = new HashSet<>(
      Arrays.asList("wikipedia.org", "github.com", "stackoverflow.com")
    );
    
    URL aUrl = new URL(url);
    String host = aUrl.getHost();
    
    // Resolve hostname to IP for verification
    InetAddress addr = InetAddress.getByName(host);
    String ipAddress = addr.getHostAddress();
    
    // Check if IP is private/reserved
    if (isPrivateOrReservedIP(ipAddress)) {
